						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab pieces lying in front of the <hi rend="italic">dhvaja stambha</hi> of Narēndrēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>VELANĀṬI CHŌḌA (GONKA II).</p>						

						<p>1179 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Śaka 1101 <hi rend="italic">(sōm-ēshu-rudhra)</hi> corresponding to 1107 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The inscription though damaged, refers to the geneology of the king Velanānṭi Chōḍa Gonka (II) and describes him as the follower of Kākatīya Gaṇapati <hi rend="italic">(Gaṇapati kshitīsam samsēvya)</hi> and further records the gift of land measuring 30 <hi rend="italic">(Dā ?)</hi> for the maintenance of <hi rend="italic">havi-bali-archana</hi> to the god Narēndrēśvara mahādēva. It also records the gift of lands by different persons (mentioned) obviously to the same god.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
